    <!-- PLACES TO VISIT SECTION -->
    <div id="feature-section">
        <h1 class="feature-section-title"> The top places to visit in <i>Karnataka</i></h1>
        <div class="feature-content">
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Karnataka/Coorg.jpg">
                <h3> Coorg </h3>
                <p> Coorg, also known as Kodagu, is a beautiful hill station in the Indian state of Karnataka. It is famous for its coffee plantations, steep hills, countless streams, rich flora & fauna, lush forests and breathtaking views. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Karnataka/Mysore.jpg">
                <h3> Mysore </h3>
                <p> Mysore is one of the major cities in the South Indian state of Karnataka. Till independence it was the capital city of Wodeyars, the erstwhile Maharajas of Mysore.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Karnataka/ShivanaSamudraFalls.jpg">
                <h3> Shivana Samudra Falls </h3>
                <p> The falls are at their best during the monsoon season i.e. from June to September. These are also known as Siva Samudram literally meaning Shiva's Sea.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Karnataka/Gokarna.jpg">
                <h3> Gokarna </h3>
                <p> Gokarna is known for the beaches. The Gokarna main beach is in town and Kudle beach are west facing.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
